to\": 1061}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"disorder\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1107}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his first interview since the second round of legislative elections on 7 July, Macron acknowledged the defeat of the outgoing presidential majority, while emphasising that no party or coalition currently had a sufficient majority to form a government.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1193, \"end\": 1199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.246233343627571e-43, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his first interview\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1133}, {\"ngram\": \"the second round\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1156}, {\"ngram\": \"legislative elections\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1181}, {\"ngram\": \"7 July\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"the defeat\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"the outgoing presidential majority\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"no party\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"coalition\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"a sufficient majority\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"a government\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1364}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reactions were not long in coming from the leaders of the Left, united within the Nouveau Front populaire (NFP), which came out on top in the election.\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_Front_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999994742730923, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Front populaire\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_Front_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_Front_(France)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Reactions\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"the leaders\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"the Left\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1429}, {\"ngram\": \"NFP\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1501}, {\"ngram\": \"the election\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They condemned the president's \\\"authoritarian drift\\\" and his \\\"policy of the worst\\\", and called on him to \\\"respect the vote of the French people\\\".\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1664, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1649, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the president's \\\"authoritarian drift\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1570}, {\"ngram\": \"his \\\"policy\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1587}, {\"ngram\": \"the vote\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1641}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After almost three weeks of fruitless negotiations, La France Insoumise (LFI), the Communist Party (PC), the Greens, and the Socialist Party (PS) agreed an hour before the president spoke to propose the largely unknown Lucie Castets for the post of prime minister.\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1718, \"end\": 1737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_France_Insoumise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.897506773609263e-16, \"text\": \"La France Insoumise\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_France_Insoumise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_France_Insoumise\"}, {\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Communist_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.06228420346