 \"the presidential coalition\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2874}, {\"ngram\": \"its core\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 2886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A first step seems to have already been taken with the recent presentation by Laurent Wauquiez, chairman of the Republican Right group in the National Assembly (DR, formerly Les R\\u00e9publicains) of an \\\"emergency legislative pact\\\" detailing the laws the party could support without formally participating in a government led by Macron's coalition.\", \"from\": 2889, \"to\": 3232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2967, \"end\": 2983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Wauquiez\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laurent Wauquiez\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Wauquiez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Wauquiez\"}, {\"begin\": 3001, \"end\": 3011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999999998935891, \"rank\": 1.0654258747877788e-10, \"text\": \"Republican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 3031, \"end\": 3048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Assembly\", \"score\": 0.9999999077022081, \"rank\": 8.716386047269537e-08, \"text\": \"National Assembly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Assembly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Assembly\"}, {\"begin\": 3063, \"end\": 3079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Republicans_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999761644179, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Les R\\u00e9publicains\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Republicans_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Republicans_(France)\"}, {\"begin\": 3213, \"end\": 3219, \"titl